parameters:
\N<Rozaro>Hey! Are you okay!? What happened here!? Pull yourself
together!

\N<Rozaro>This smell... the scent of the blood of the monsters that
infest this place, huh. I see... she must have managed to
take them down but then got caught up in her own defensive
instincts afterward.
\N<Rozaro>Even so... why is she here all alone in such a place...

\N<Rozaro>...No matter how much she wants to be strong for her family,
why would she do something so reckless...

\N<Rozaro>...She's in a deep sleep. It seems she's been exposed to a
considerable amount of poison. I hope she wakes up safely...

\N<Rozaro>...Is it my fault? If I had stopped her more forcefully back
then, she wouldn't be in a place like this...

\N<Rozaro>But... her determination was real. I truly felt there was no
need for me to dampen her spirits.

\N<Rozaro>...This is no time for regrets or self-questioning. Right
now, I need to ensure Segi-san's safety...

\N<Rozaro>It's okay... she's breathing. She's just unconscious. At
this rate, she should wake up soon...

\N<Rozaro>Even so... it's good that I was the one who found her
unconscious. If it had been someone else... the thought
gives me chills.

\N<Rozaro>No... wait? How long has she been lying here? How can I be
sure that I was the first to find her?

\N<Rozaro>That's right... what if some wicked person had found her in
this state before me? Can I be certain that such a
possibility doesn't exist...?
\N<Rozaro>...I must check. I have to make sure...

\N<Rozaro>That's right... I was the one who told her about this place.
If something happened to her, I couldn't face Yuia as a
friend.

\N<Rozaro>Not yet... she's still unconscious. I must check more
carefully now while making sure not to hurt her.

\N<Rozaro>It's okay... there's some disarray in her clothing, but
there are no signs of tampering or violence.

\N<Rozaro>Good... that's a relief. If something had happened to her...
what would I have said to Yuia and Riia...

\N<Segi>Eh...ah. Rozaro-san? Why are you here...? And where is this
place...?

\N<Rozaro>...It seems you're still a bit out of it. You were collapsed
here. You probably got caught up in the self-defense
instincts of the ruins' creatures.

\N<Segi>Th-that's right... I... got caught up in that creature's
explosion...
\N<Segi>Eh...um... Did you, Rozaro-san, take care of me...?

\N<Rozaro>Yes. I was worried about you. After we parted, I came to
check on you and found you lying here unconscious.

\N<Segi>Is that so... I must have caused you quite a bit of trouble
without realizing it... I'm sorry.

\N<Rozaro>No... don't worry about it. I bear some responsibility for
this situation as well.

\N<Segi>I'm sorry...! For showing you something so inappropriate...
I...!

\N<Rozaro>No... it's fine. When you were unconscious, there was a
slight disarray in your clothing.

\N<Rozaro>So I had you wear my coat. My apologies for doing so without
asking.

\N<Segi>No, it's... I'm the one who should apologize for showing
such an unsightly appearance...

\N<Rozaro>I understand your resolve to become strong to confront Lyuda
and protect Yuia and Riia.

\N<Rozaro>But... is it truly the right thing to do? Is it necessary
for you to go this far?

\N<Rozaro>What would Yuia and your son have done if something had
happened to you?

\N<Rozaro>You're intelligent and family-oriented. I'm sure you
wouldn't take any meaningless actions that would make your
family sad without me having to say it. Would you mind
telling me your reasons?

\N<Segi>I told you before... that by leaving something very
important to someone else, I ended up losing everything,
right?

\N<Segi>That's why... I thought it wasn't enough to just be
protected...

\N<Segi>...Yes. Yuia-sama told me. No matter what happens, he would
definitely protect me and my son.

\N<Segi>I was happy to hear such strong words from the person I
love.

\N<Segi>But... on the flip side, that also means imposing great pain
and sorrow on Yuia-sama.

\N<Segi>It's one thing for my son, but I couldn't just stay in a
safe place and be comfortably protected... That's what I
thought.

\N<Segi>But... as you can see, this is the result. In the end, I was
saved by you.

\N<Segi>It's nothing but my own weakness. If you hadn't saved me, by
now I might have been...

\N<Rozaro>It's not surprising. Even though this is a training facility
for appraisal, the creatures nesting here are not opponents
one can fight without proper training, especially not for a
woman like you.

\N<Rozaro>The only exception where your strength could fight them
would be if you had their equipment... Lyuda's military
gear.

\N<Rozaro>Yes, the weapons they carry are laced with a poison that
drives the nerves that trigger the monsters' self-defense
mechanisms mad. If you can master using that, fighting here
wouldn't be impossible.

\N<Rozaro>That said, you should first return to your family. They must
be worried about you.

\N<Segi>Yes, you're right... I understand. Thank you very much for
saving me.
\N<Rozaro>No... As a warrior, as a man... I only did what was natural.

\N<Segi>What's this... I feel a little dizzy... Maybe it's because
of the toxic air in the ruins...?

\N<Segi>More importantly... it's getting late. I have to go home or
they'll both be worried...

\N<Segi>Wha... What... What is this...!? It has a different aura
from the other monsters...!

\N<Segi>So... that's it... This is his lair. And if I can defeat
him, maybe that will complete the evaluation Ryuda was
talking about...
\N<Segi>Then... I have to do it. To become stronger.

\N<Segi>I have no grudge against you... but now, I must turn my
blade towards you.
\N<Segi>For Riia. For Lord Yuia. And for myself...

\N<Segi>So... that's right... I'm sure... some of the monsters here
have a self-defense instinct... or something...!

\N<Segi>This must be his...! Self-defense... instinct as he faces
his death throes...!
